transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling, this is Charles.

Speaker 2: Hi Charles, this is George Milutinovich.

Speaker 1: I received a refill on a prescription that I didn't, a prescription that I didn't order.

Speaker 2: I had called and cancelled the autofill several months ago, so...

Speaker 1: Can I get your phone number please?

Speaker 2: It's 559-289-0067.

Speaker 1: Okay, George in Fresno, California?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me see here, I have...

Speaker 2: that the side effects...

Speaker 1: from the first ones that you were getting were a little too much,

Speaker 2: so we sent you out the AGV for free to try.

Speaker 1: How did you like those?

Speaker 2: Well, it's great except I've had a couple of heart attacks,

Speaker 1: and I'm just, yeah, things aren't going well for me right now.

Speaker 2: Okay, we really didn't know.

Speaker 1: It looks like the way everything was set up was so that you get it like every,

Speaker 2: like once a year basically, once every six months.

Speaker 1: So, sorry to hear about the heart attack, brother.

Speaker 2: I'll make sure everything is cancelled.

Speaker 1: What you're going to do, if you want the money back,

Speaker 2: or you want to keep it for later on down the line,

Speaker 1: they have a pretty long shelf life, like three years,

Speaker 2: the Southgate, Kentucky address that's on the pill bottle,

Speaker 1: send everything back to them, or if it's still in the packaging,

Speaker 2: put it back in the packaging, seal it up real, real tight,

Speaker 1: write return to sender on it, put it back in the mailbox,

Speaker 2: mailman will take it and send it back to us for free,

Speaker 1: and you'll get the money back as soon as we get the pills back.

Speaker 2: You know, honestly, God, I'm going to, just to be hopeful,

Speaker 1: I'm going to hold on to it, but I want to please make sure

Speaker 2: that I don't get any more, okay, until I...

Speaker 1: Understood. Yeah, give me one second.

Speaker 2: Let me check the shelf life just so I'm 100%.

Speaker 1: Shelf life for generic viagra, AGV, two to three years, yeah.

Speaker 2: So, if the doctor gives you the okay, try them out and then...

Speaker 1: Good deal.

Speaker 2: Yeah, call us when you're hot and ready, all right?

Speaker 1: Oh, boy, thank you very much.

Speaker 2: Absolutely, hope you have a great one, brother.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
